{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_220","type":"agent_message","text":"The newest miss is mailbox/queue semantics loaded from Pekko’s default mailbox bindings, which is exactly the kind of config-driven cluster worth batching. I’m adding the dispatch semantics types and mailbox classes referenced in `reference.conf`, plus the `dispatch` package to the allowlist, so we don’t keep paying for one-class-at-a-time rebuilds there."}}
